      <h1 class='title'>Child Poverty</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 18 December 2003 vol 415 cc154-5WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_154ws' title='Col. 154WS &mdash; HC Deb 18 December 2003 vol 415 c154WS' name='column_154ws' href='#column_154ws' rel='bookmark'>154WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0415P2_20031218_CWS_16'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-andrew-smith' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0415P2_20031218_CWS_16' title='Link to this speech by Mr Andrew Smith' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-andrew-smith" title="Mr Andrew Smith">The Secretary of State for Work and Pensions (Mr. Andrew Smith)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">I have today published "Measuring Child Poverty". A copy has been placed in the Library.</p><p>The Government issued a consultation document in April 2002 to promote debate on how best to build on their existing indicators to measure child poverty in the long term. The document published today outlines a long-term measure of child poverty for the UK. Our conclusions are based on a thorough analysis of the responses to the consultation document and further methodological work. None of this affects any of our existing PSA's which we remain committed to.</p><p>Our new measure of child poverty will consist of: absolute low income&#x2014;to measure whether the poorest families are seeing their incomes rise in real terms; relative low income&#x2014;to measure whether the poorest families are keeping pace with the growth of incomes in the economy as a whole and material deprivation and low income combined&#x2014;to provide a wider measure of
          
          <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_155ws' title='Col. 155WS &mdash; HC Deb 18 December 2003 vol 415 c155WS' name='column_155ws' href='#column_155ws' rel='bookmark'>155WS</a>
          people's living standards. Using this measure, poverty is falling when all three indicators are moving in the right direction.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
